javelin.controller.quality.resistance

Class EnergyImmunity

  • java.lang.Object
    • javelin.controller.quality.Quality
      • javelin.controller.quality.resistance.EnergyImmunity

  • public class EnergyImmunity
extends Quality
    This is a tricky one because since we're treating all energy types as the same one, and this is a high-rated special quality at 1cr per energy type, it means that any monster with a immunity immediately is at least level 5 - including, for example, a Small Skeleton. Initially this was meant to flag Monster.energyresistance as Integer.MAX_VALUE but to counter the problem above we're simply adding the equivalent of 1CR as EnergyResistance instead. Units can still have true immunity to all energy types through the EnergyImmunityUpgrade.
